Installation:

    git clone git://github.com/dmayle/dotfiles.git ~/.dotfiles

Create symlinks:

    ln -s .dotfiles/vim ~/.vim
    ln -s .dotfiles/bash/bashrc ~/.bashrc
    ln -s .dotfiles/bash/bashrc ~/.bash_profile
    ln -s .dotfiles/bash/aliases ~/.bash_aliases
    ln -s .dotfiles/inputrc ~/.inputrc
    ln -s .dotfiles/editrc ~/.editrc
    ln -s .vim/vimrc ~/.vimrc

Switch to the `~/.dotfiles` directory, and fetch submodules:

    cd ~/.dotfiles
    git submodule update --init

Add this to your crontab to auto-update everyday at 3am.
    0 3 * * * (cd ~/.dotfiles && (git pull https://github.com/dmayle/dotfiles; git submodule update --init)) &>/dev/null

Software required:
    Mac:
        MacVim (in order to get a vim compiled with python and ruby support)
        Exuberant Ctags (the BSD ctags that comes with OSX is bad)
